                            the JELLY BEAN FACTORY
                           ------------------------



  Requirements
  ------------

       In order to run properly, the JELLY BEAN FACTORY requires the
  following:

      - 286 MINIMUM, 386 highly recommended for good quality music
      - VGA card
      - a hard drive with at least 1.2 Megs of free space
      - 370k RAM min., 540k for full music and sound effects

  In addition, the JELLY BEAN FACTORY also supports:

      - SOUND BLASTER for digitized music and sound effects
      - SOUND BLASTER PRO for STEREO digitized music and sound effects
      - Joystick

  WARNING: the JELLY BEAN FACTORY was not designed to run under Windows,
           OS/2 or desqview, and as such, will not work properly when
           run from them.

  NOTE: If the game is operating slow, then try decreasing the sound quality
        option in the config program (see setup and sound card details).


  Installation
  ------------

       Before you can play the JELLY BEAN FACTORY, you must first run
  INSTALL.EXE to extract the files, and set up your sound card and input
  device.  The installation program will ask for the drive and directory
  you want the JELLY BEAN FACTORY installed to.  Installation could take up
  to six minutes depending on computer speed, so be patient.



  Setup
  -----

       The setup program is automatically executed at the end of the
  installation process.  To customize the setup configuration, run the
  program CONFIG.EXE.  The following briefly explains the setup options.
      Sound Card
      ----------

             If you have a SOUND BLASTER, SOUND BLASTER PRO, or
        compatible sound card, then you can enjoy the full gaming
        experience with the excellent digitized music and sound effects.
        NOTE: If you do not have such a sound card, then be sure to
              select NO SOUND at the sound card menu option.
 
             Pro Audio Spectrum users must select the Sound Blaster
        option in the setup program, and choose the settings
        corresponding to the SOUND BLASTER section of the card.  Refer
        to your sound card manual for more information.


      Input Device
      ------------

             This is where you select whether you want to use the
        keyboard or a joystick.  If you select joystick, and one is not
        available when the game is loaded, then it will return to
        keyboard operation.

             If you choose to use a joystick, it will ask you to center
        the joystick and press any key, and then to move the joystick in
        all directions, and press any key.


      Sound Quality
      -------------

             This game uses special digitized music which requires a lot
        of the CPU's time, and because of this, this option has been
        added so that slower computers can still enjoy the great music
        and sound effects.  For better sound clarity, use a higher setting.
        For a slow computer, try using the lower settings (6-10 kHz),
        and slowly increase the setting until the game runs slower.
		NOTE: It IS possible that some slow computers will not even be able to
              handle the lowest quality setting.


  Loading the JELLY BEAN FACTORY
  ------------------------------

       Once the JELLY BEAN FACTORY has been installed, type JELLY to load
  the game.



  Playing the Game
  ----------------

      Object of the Game
      ------------------

             To clear the most beans off the screen by aligning them by
        color, horizontally, verticaly, or diagonally, as they fall,
        before the screen fills up.
             After your game ends, a gameover screen will appear.  To
        continue, press escape, enter, or the spaceber.

             If you attained a high score, you will then be asked for
        your initials.  After entering your initials, press escape or
        enter to return to the main menu.


      Types of Beans
      --------------

             "Normal" Beans - These beans are all one color and fall in
        combination with two other randomly selected beans.  These can be
        cleared away by aligning three or more beans of the same color,
        horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.

             "Clearing" Beans - (pulsing blue beans) When you drop a set
        of clearing beans, all of the beans on screen that are the same
        color as the bean below, the clearing beans, will be cleared.

             "Reject" Beans - (striped beans)
        Once in a while the factory will produce reject beans.
        These can only be cleared away with the clearing beans.

      Keys Active During Game Play
      ----------------------------

         Up/Down       - Changes the bean order
         Left/Right    - Moves the beans
         Space/Enter   - Drops the beans
         Center        - Turns the beans vertically or horizontally
            (#5 key on numeric keypad)
         Escape        - Aborts the current game
         F1            - Pauses current game
         F2            - Toggles music & sound effects on/off
         F3            - Toggles sound effects on/off
         F4            - Toggles fast clear on/off



  Using The Joystick
  ------------------

     Up/Down       - Same as Up/Down arrow keys
     Left/Right    - Same as Left/Right arrow keys
     Button 1      - Same as Space Bar or Enter Key
     Button 2      - Same as center key on numeric key pad
     Both buttons  - Same as Escape Key


